 NORTHERN
CAPE cops closed down a drug laboratory in West End in Kimberley. The
Organised Crime Unit from Northern Cape Provincial Detectives received intel about
a flat used as a drug lab. Police
spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Dimakatso Mooi said upon searching the buildings
the cops found drugs, chemicals, scales, packaging equipment and various empty
chemical containers. “The flat
was cleaned out and all confiscated drugs and equipment are estimated to the
value of R10 million. “While the
police were busy with the search, a suspicious person was noticed passing near
the flat and was immediately stopped and searched,” Mooi said. Tik drugs worth
an estimated street value of R2 500 were found in his possession. Mooi said
the 33-year-old suspect was arrested and is expected to appear before
Magistrates’ Court soon on a charge of dealing in drugs. Provincial
Commissioner of Northern Cape Province Lieutenant General Risimati Peter
Shivuri commended the police for their sterling work done.